On the other hand, on the Wall Street Journal forum we find comments saying that it is irresponsible to have children if you do not know what you are going to feed them with.
The protesters who launched the movement Thursday at 6:30 a.m. near McDonald's on 40th Street and Madison Avenue demanded that cashiers and fast-food cooks be paid at least $15 an hour, more than twice the current minimum wage.
