It is here that the Caucasian ethnic group named Talysh lives, about which little is known, except that they speak Persian and Azerbaijani perfectly and have a very long life.
Terminus: Lerik.
The small town stands out with its too aggressive Soviet-era architecture that does not match the picturesque mountain landscape at all.
European tourists are rare here, the journey from the capital of Azerbaijan, Baku, is much too painful.
